# Daily Diary - Day 06

## Methods & Functions

### Today's Topics
- Method Declaration & Definition
- Method Parameters & Return Types
- Method Overloading
- Recursion Basics
- Method Calling Stack

### Practical Work
- Created multiple methods with different return types
- Implemented method overloading examples
- Built recursive functions (factorial, Fibonacci)
- Practiced static vs instance methods

### Code Example
```java
public class MethodsDemo {
    
    // Simple method
    public static void greet() {
        System.out.println("Hello World!");
    }
    
    // Method with parameters and return type
    public static int add(int a, int b) {
        return a + b;
    }
    
    // Method overloading
    public static double add(double a, double b) {
        return a + b;
    }
    
    // Recursive method
    public static int factorial(int n) {
        if (n == 0) return 1;
        return n * factorial(n - 1);
    }
    
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        greet();
        System.out.println("Sum: " + add(5, 3));
        System.out.println("Factorial: " + factorial(5));
    }
}
